text: building ont his thought, and i bet it’s already happening, <@U0EL0GLEL> can you dedicate the morning to additional experience testing before we go through it as a group later?  you’ve got a critical eye and the more sweeps, the better
Yep was looking into that this morning
i figured.  Can you share out and tag <@U02E3CRMA> and i your findings?  put em in dev channel.  every bit of due diligence counts at this point
and further, let me know if i can help before the formal QA this afternoon

<!here|@here>: i wanna keep some of the positive thoughts/memories coming.  lots of thoughts in me were drummed up AFTER the retrospective.  feel free to join in.  

I’m happy with all of the upfront work people like <@U0260V4K1> and <@U0HPGQ4KH> put in to consider the wall dimensions and ergonomics early on.  Pretty spectacular how well that works when built out to scale.
Also happy with how much room wound up in between the wall and the front doors of BL space

<!here|@here>: BrandLab also uploaded video for end of day yesteray (might wanna watch at 2x speed) <https://docs.google.com/a/uncorkedstudios.com/spreadsheets/d/1OpvRMtf5dhKcbV_DGO8-2fmiqpgcmM9D-Pi-oVOQ7O8/edit?usp=sharing>  3/6 participants closed door at end.  we’re working with client to chronicle the interactions

<@U0ML49XU0|dennishanley> shared a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/dennishanley/F1XKUMPR8/sanbrunocubbywall-post-launchsprintplanningandreleasenotes-parkinglot|San Bruno Cubby Wall - Post-Launch Sprint Planning and Release Notes>
